// verbose: true
// exceptionClass: BuildingException
// msgContains: Cannot resolve 'Foobar'
// position: 7/8

\problem {
   \<{ Foobar x = null; }\> true
}

// The Java block refers to an unknown type. Previously the resulting
// UnsolvedSymbolException escaped without any location pointing into the
// .key file (ExceptionTools.getLocation returned null). Now the error is
// wrapped with the modality's location and the JavaParser jargon
// ("Unsolved symbol : Foobar") is humanized to the same "Cannot resolve ..."
// wording KeY uses elsewhere.
